</div><div class="post post_micro is_regular post_tumblelog_7652712883a78ee0a7e928bbd177f97e not_mine is_original with_permalink no_source has_hover" id="post_micro_3141052776"  data-post-id='3141052776' data-root-id='3141052776' data-tumblelog-name='tymkrs' data-tumblelog-key='PpptURJ1M' data-reblog-key='iqJuMZVq' data-type='regular' data-serve-id='0.43217300 14060420251237406883' data-json='{"post-id":"3141052776","root-id":"3141052776","tumblelog-name":"tymkrs","tumblelog-key":"PpptURJ1M","reblog-key":"iqJuMZVq","type":"regular","serve-id":"0.43217300 14060420251237406883","json":"{\u0022post-id\u0022:\u00223141052776\u0022,\u0022root-id\u0022:\u00223141052776\u0022,\u0022tumblelog-name\u0022:\u0022tymkrs\u0022,\u0022tumblelog-key\u0022:\u0022PpptURJ1M\u0022,\u0022reblog-key\u0022:\u0022iqJuMZVq\u0022,\u0022type\u0022:\u0022regular\u0022,\u0022serve-id\u0022:\u00220.43217300 14060420251237406883\u0022}"}'><div class="post_content"><div class="post_content_inner"><div class="post_title">DIY Netcasting Studio - Part 3: Gutted!</div><p><p><a href="http://tymkrs.tumblr.com/post/3141052776/diy-netcasting-studio-part-3-gutted"><img src="http://assets.tumblr.com/images/inline_placeholder.png" width="18" height="14"/></a></p>  <p>  Today we are ripping things apart! We&#8217;ve removed the drop ceiling, removed a florescent light, most of the faux wood paneling, and conducted a cursory inspection of what we have to work with under the cheap make up.</p>We&#8217;ll be building a sound proof room inside this room, filming progress as it&#8217;s made. We post new videos every few days so please subscribe!<p></p>In time, this room will serve as a sound stage for our video production with integrated mic booms, camera mounts, and lighting. We&#8217;ll be showing you guys all of the tips and tricks we&#8217;ve picked up over the years.If you want extra daily content about us, our projects, and the production of these videos be sure to follow us on Twitter. You can always find links to all of our stuff at <a href="http://about.me/tymkrs" title="http://about.me/tymkrs" target="_blank">http://about.me/tymkrs</a> or individually at these pages:<p></p><a href="http://tymkrs.com/" title="http://tymkrs.com/" target="_blank">http://tymkrs.com/</a><br /><a href="http://twitter.com/tymkrs" title="http://twitter.com/tymkrs" target="_blank">http://twitter.com/tymkrs</a><br /><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/tymkrs/" title="http://www.flickr.com/photos/tymkrs/" target="_blank">http://www.flickr.com/photos/tymkrs/</a><br /><a href="http://tymkrs.tumblr.com/" title="http://tymkrs.tumblr.com/" target="_blank">http://tymkrs.tumblr.com/</a>We love hanging out with you guys on Twitter while working on our projects and these videos. Life is so much more fun with good company. Don&#8217;t hesitate to message us! As you can see, we do read them, and do our best to answer!<p></p>If you would like to help support our ability to make many more programs like this one, please share this video. We need you! Steven Seagal is trending on Twitter instead of something worthwhile like #555contest. Come on geeks!!! Tweet and ReTweet - it costs you nothing and helps save future generations from becoming idiots! It&#8217;s a geek revolution, take back the media!  <p>  <ul></ul></p>  </p></div></div><div class="post_glass post_micro_glass" 
